Barnaby's family: Brutally murdered in a single night of violence within their own home. The body of Caleb was never recovered. Their house now stands empty, whispered to be a place of restless spirits, a place no sane villager would dare to tread.

Fitch and Garth: Skilled hunters, entered the nearby woods and never returned. Their disappearance, unexplained and complete, casts a shadow over the village.

Falco: Fisherman's son seeking a better life in the city, found himself entangled in a dangerous romance with the daughter of a wealthy gambling den owner. Accused of multiple murders he did not commit, he now carries a 100 gold bounty on his head.

